This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it deals with the task of localizing objects in images based on natural language expressions. The use of a neural network and syntactic analysis also suggests that it could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of tracking and localization suggests that it could also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
